  "rationale": "Target: at least 20 examples per controlled feature (6 features x 20 = 120 images). The '20 per feature' figure is practitioner folklore from the LoRA-training community (most-cited starting count for a character/concept LoRA; no paper states it). DreamBooth (arXiv:2208.12242) needs only 3-5/subject and Concept Sliders (github.com/rohitgandikota/sliders) ~4-6 pairs/attribute, so 20/feature is the LoRA-specific rule, not universal.",
  "v3_design_principle": "User: 'it's easier to control the feature if you can reduce the number of features in an image output.' v3 therefore uses ATOMIC features — every feature varies exactly ONE attribute against a fixed baseline (orange hair, white crop top + brown skirt + leather boots, plain background). silver_hair changes only hair color (baseline outfit); each outfit feature changes only the outfit (baseline hair); no setting/lighting deltas mixed in. This replaces v1/v2's composite features (e.g. silver_kimono = hair delta + outfit delta at once; autumn_sunset = braids + jacket + forest + sunset light).",
